Comment.value:
when selected by the person he gave the ring to

plot not completed

for the purposes of the template plot, the "NW_Resc_Plot" global is set as follows:
0 = plot not completed
10 = prisoner NPC found but not brought yet
50 = prisoner NPC killed
100 = prisoner NPC rescued (this is set by a trigger at the entrance to the area)
200 = plot giver NPC is leaving

if Meldanen is alive
he leaves the area permanently

plot not done
he has not given away the ring
speaker is of evil alignment or low charisma

give the ring to the speaker
set the locals so that the job has been accepted

alternatively, this information could be more vague, as in a 'general area' the party has to search
OR the rescue plot giver could direct the PC to someone who might know more
either way, this information is only given to a PC who has accepted the plot, not on this response
